SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 184
By Yager
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of John Charles McNeeley
of Andersonville.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the untimely passing of John Charles McNeeley; and
WHEREAS, John McNeeley was a beloved friend and neighbor who did his utmost to
improve the well-being of all who were blessed to know him; and
WHEREAS, the son of Charles E. McNeeley and Debra Hobbs McNeeley, he was a
1996 graduate of Campbell County High School, where he was a proud member of the Cougars
basketball team during three consecutive district championships, from 1994 to 1996; he went on
to play basketball at the collegiate level, earning an athletic scholarship at Walters State
Community College; and
WHEREAS, Mr. McNeeley continued his education at East Tennessee State University,
where he was a member of Pi Kappa Alpha fraternity, which he served as president; after
graduation, he began his career with UPS, working there for many years before transitioning to
a role at Avex Flight Support; and
WHEREAS, since 2012, he had served as a Tennessee licensed funeral director and
worked alongside his family at Walters Funeral Home; and
WHEREAS, apart from his vocational pursuits, he enjoyed woodworking and crafting
items that he then gifted to friends and family members; he evinced his religious faith as a
charter member of New Horizon Baptist Church; and
WHEREAS, he was also deeply devoted to his family and always endeavored to remain
true to family values of the highest order; and
