WHEREAS, in addition to his mother, John McNeeley is survived by his wife, Andrea
Tegan McRae McNeeley; beloved son, John Connor McNeeley; brother, Brent (Ashlie)
McNeeley; nieces, Ava Claire McNeeley, Abby Day, and Ella Day; nephew, Nicholas Reynolds;
aunts, Doris Hobbs (Randall) Fields and Karen McNeeley (Chris) Brown, and Kenneth (Sheila)
McNeeley; cousins, Stephen (Holly) Fields, Derek (Yessica) McNeeley, Cory McNeeley, Kendra
(Spenser) St. John, Tyler (Polly) Johnson, and Adam Johnson; mother-in-law and father-in-law,
Melissa and Dennis Reynolds; sister-in-law, Kyla (Gabe Day) Reynolds; brother-in-law, Elliot
(Sheena) Reynolds; and numerous other extended family members and friends; and
WHEREAS, in addition to his father, he was preceded in death by his grandparents,
Clyde and Josie McNeeley and Lonnie and Ruby Hobbs; uncles, Warren Gene Hobbs and
William Paul "Bill" McNeeley; father-in-law, Eddie McRae; and special grandparents-in-law, Ann
and Pete McRae; and
WHEREAS, throughout his many worthy endeavors, John McNeeley distinguished
himself as a beacon of kindness and wisdom; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should pay tribute to the bountiful life of this exceptional
Tennessean; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of John Charles McNeeley,
reflecting fondly upon his ability to live the examined life with courage and conviction.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we extend our sympathy and condolences to the
family and friends of Mr. McNeeley.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
